article_title: HEARD ON THE STREET: Google's I/O Pitch is Worth Buying
article_text:
More than selling gadgets, Google's main job at its developers' conference each year is to promote its relevance.

This is no small matter. While the Internet heavyweight generates more headlines for its attempts at mobile phones, TV boxes and robot cars, Google remains dependent on advertising for about 90% of its revenue. To keep those ad dollars flowing, it must ensure users keep interacting with its properties no matter what...

twitter.description: Google's latest I/O conference was short on new branded hardware, but it keeps the company relevant, which is what counts with investors.
twitter.title: Google's I/O Pitch is Worth Buying
